---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const B = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Start here"
  description="Three guided entry points into Extended Matrix — pick the one that fits your work."
>
  <section class="start">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="tag">Start here</span>
      <h1 class="start__title">Pick your entry point.</h1>
      <p class="start__sub">
        Extended Matrix is a method (the formal language), a framework (a
        family of open-source tools), and a community. Three short paths
        below — each leads you straight to where the work happens.
      </p>

      <div class="paths">
        <article class="path">
          <header>
            <span class="path__num">1</span>
            <h2>Sources, stratigraphy, reconstruction</h2>
            <p class="path__who">For archaeologists, heritage scholars, students.</p>
          </header>
          <p>
            Begin with the formal language: it is what you will read, write
            and discuss when reasoning about evidence. Pencil and paper are
            enough to start.
          </p>
          <ol class="path__steps">
            <li>
              Read the <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/en/1.5.0dev/learn_EM.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                Learn EM</a> guide.
            </li>
            <li>
              Walk through <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/en/1.5.0dev/stratigraphic_nodes.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                stratigraphic nodes</a> and <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/en/1.5.0dev/paradata_nodes.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                paradata nodes</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              Hands-on: <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/tutorials/12-install-yed-blender.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                install yEd with the EM palette</a> and draw your first graph.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p class="path__cross">
            <a href={`${B}/tools/#archaeologist`}>→ Tools for archaeologists</a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="path">
          <header>
            <span class="path__num">2</span>
            <h2>3D models annotated with EM data</h2>
            <p class="path__who">For 3D artists, modellers, technical-archaeologists.</p>
          </header>
          <p>
            Bring an existing graph into Blender, link proxies to stratigraphic
            units, drive visualisation by epoch and property, export to the
            web.
          </p>
          <ol class="path__steps">
            <li>
              <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/installation.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                Install EM Tools</a> (Blender extension).
            </li>
            <li>
              Follow <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/tutorials/13-first-matrix-creation.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                creating your first matrix</a>, then the
              <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/tutorials/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                intermediate tutorial track</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              Publish to the web with <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/heriverse/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                Heriverse</a>.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p class="path__cross">
            <a href={`${B}/tools/#modeller`}>→ Tools for 3D modellers</a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="path">
          <header>
            <span class="path__num">3</span>
            <h2>Extend, integrate, contribute</h2>
            <p class="path__who">For developers and tool-builders.</p>
          </header>
          <p>
            EM is implemented as a Python knowledge-graph library
            (<code>s3dgraphy</code>) you can plug into any platform — Revit,
            3ds Max, Unity, Unreal, custom pipelines.
          </p>
          <ol class="path__steps">
            <li>
              <code>pip install s3dgraphy</code> and read the
              <a href="https://github.com/zalmoxes-laran/s3dgraphy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                repository README</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              For the Blender add-on, see
              <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/development_setup.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                development setup</a> and
              <a href="https://docs.extendedmatrix.org/projects/EM-tools/en/latest/api_reference.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                API reference</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              Open an issue or join the
              <a href="https://t.me/UserGroupEM" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Telegram group</a>.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p class="path__cross">
            <a href={`${B}/tools/#developer`}>→ Tools for developers</a>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p class="start__foot">
        Still unsure?
        <a href="https://t.me/UserGroupEM" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ask the community →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .start { padding: 80px 0 60px; }
  .start__title { margin: 14px 0 18px; }
  .start__sub {
    max-width: 640px;
    color: var(--em-text-muted);
    font-size: 17px;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }
  .paths {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 28px;
  }
  .path {
    border: 1px solid var(--em-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 32px 32px 28px;
    background: var(--em-bg);
  }
  .path header {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
    column-gap: 20px;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .path__num {
    grid-row: span 2;
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--em-gold-tint);
    color: var(--em-gold);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 800;
  }
  .path header h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .path__who {
    grid-column: 2;
    margin: 4px 0 0;
    color: var(--em-text-muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .path > p {
    margin: 8px 0 16px;
    color: var(--em-text);
  }
  .path__steps {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: step;
    padding-left: 0;
  }
  .path__steps li {
    counter-increment: step;
    position: relative;
    padding: 8px 0 8px 38px;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--em-border);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--em-text);
  }
  .path__steps li:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .path__steps li::before {
    content: counter(step);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 9px;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    background: var(--em-navy);
    color: var(--em-bg);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .path__cross {
    margin: 14px 0 0;
    padding-top: 12px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--em-border);
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .path__cross a {
    color: var(--em-gold);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .start__foot {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 56px;
    color: var(--em-text-muted);
  }
  .start__foot a {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--em-gold);
  }

  @media (min-width: 800px) {
    .paths { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
